<p>I have a MySQL table</p>  <pre><code>discount_vouchers ------------------ id email test_id </code></pre>  <p>My goal is to list all vouchers that appears more than once with a given email and a given test_id from the GROUP BY:</p>  <pre><code>GROUP BY email, test_id HAVING count(*) &gt;1 </code></pre>  <p>How to get read of this group by?</p>  <p>Here is an example:</p>  <pre><code>discount_vouchers ------------------ 1    1@test.com    20 2    1@test.com    10 3    1@test.com    20 4    2@test.com    30 </code></pre>  <p>I would like to have as a result:</p>  <pre><code>id     email     test_id   count 1    1@test.com    20       2 2    1@test.com    10       1 3    1@test.com    20       2 4    2@test.com    30       2 </code></pre>